  "prompt": "What do we know about \"Late Show with Stephen Colbert\"?",
  "response": "\"The Late Show with Stephen Colbert\" is an American late-night talk show and news satire program that airs on CBS. It premiered on September 8, 2015, following the retirement of David Letterman, who previously hosted \"Late Show with David Letterman\" in the same time slot.\n\nStephen Colbert, the host, rose to fame with his work on \"The Daily Show with Jon Stewart\" and later \"The Colbert Report,\" which aired on Comedy Central. Colbert's style combines humor with political and social commentary, and he often injects his personal views into the show's content. Unlike his character on \"The Colbert Report,\" Stephen Colbert appears as himself on \"The Late Show.\"\n\nThe show typically features a mix of monologues, interviews with celebrities, politicians, and other public figures, comedy sketches, and musical performances. Colbert's sharp wit and insightful commentary have made the show popular, especially among viewers interested in politics and current events. At various points, the show has achieved high ratings and significant social media traction.\n\nAdditionally, Colbert's tenure has been marked by an increase in politically charged content, particularly during the 2016 presidential election and the subsequent years, where he frequently critiqued the administration of President Donald Trump.\n\n\"The Late Show with Stephen Colbert\" is filmed at the Ed Sullivan Theater in New York City, and it follows the format of traditional late-night talk shows while integrating Colbert's unique comedic style and perspective.",
